    {
      "id": "2054605365376160030",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T16:51:06.000Z",
      "text": "Physicist Michio Kaku suggests dark matter isn’t matter at all. It is gravity leaking from a parallel dimension.",
      "screen_name": "Kekius_Sage",
      "name": "Kekius Maximus",
      "pfp_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2040407364868673536/vhyqWwNy_400x400.jpg",
      "in_reply_to_screen_names": [],
      "media": [
        {
          "type": "photo",
          "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HINrX1HboAANsXn?format=jpg&name=small"
        },
        {
          "type": "photo",
          "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HINsoffboAAFCRM?format=png&name=360x360"
        }
      ],
      "reply_count": 1662,
      "retweet_count": 3426,
      "favorite_count": 20947,
      "_source": "dom",
      "_scraped_on": "https://x.com/Kekius_Sage/status/2054605365376160030"
    },
    {
      "id": "2054605370795114535",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T16:51:07.000Z",
      "text": "Think of a two-story house. You cannot see the people living on the floor above you, but you can hear their footsteps vibrating through the ceiling.",
      "screen_name": "Kekius_Sage",
      "name": "Kekius Maximus",
      "pfp_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2040407364868673536/vhyqWwNy_400x400.jpg",
      "in_reply_to_screen_names": [],
      "media": [],
      "reply_count": 33,
      "retweet_count": 41,
      "favorite_count": 1468,
      "_source": "dom",
      "_scraped_on": "https://x.com/Kekius_Sage/status/2054605365376160030",
      "inferred_in_reply_to_id": "2054605365376160030"
    },
    {
      "id": "2054605377673863638",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T16:51:09.000Z",
      "text": "Kaku argues that dark matter is the footstep of a galaxy residing in another dimension. It interacts with our reality only through the carrier of gravity.",
      "screen_name": "Kekius_Sage",
      "name": "Kekius Maximus",
      "pfp_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2040407364868673536/vhyqWwNy_400x400.jpg",
      "in_reply_to_screen_names": [],
      "media": [],
      "reply_count": 27,
      "retweet_count": 36,
      "favorite_count": 1071,
      "_source": "dom",
      "_scraped_on": "https://x.com/Kekius_Sage/status/2054605365376160030",
      "inferred_in_reply_to_id": "2054605370795114535"
    },
    {
      "id": "2054605385210941650",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T16:51:11.000Z",
      "text": "Physics does not require the universe to be a single, isolated sheet. It only requires the system to be logically consistent. \n\nWhat we perceive as missing mass is simply the gravitational data of a neighboring universe.",
      "screen_name": "Kekius_Sage",
      "name": "Kekius Maximus",
      "pfp_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2040407364868673536/vhyqWwNy_400x400.jpg",
      "in_reply_to_screen_names": [],
      "media": [],
      "reply_count": 9,
      "retweet_count": 20,
      "favorite_count": 721,
      "_source": "dom",
      "_scraped_on": "https://x.com/Kekius_Sage/status/2054605365376160030",
      "inferred_in_reply_to_id": "2054605377673863638"
    },
    {
      "id": "2054605394576842960",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T16:51:13.000Z",
      "text": "The next revolution in cosmology won't be finding a new particle in a collider.\n\nIt will be the realization that we are living in a high dimensional stack. We are just deaf to the layers sitting right on top of us.",
      "screen_name": "Kekius_Sage",
      "name": "Kekius Maximus",
      "pfp_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2040407364868673536/vhyqWwNy_400x400.jpg",
      "in_reply_to_screen_names": [],
      "media": [],
      "reply_count": 45,
      "retweet_count": 34,
      "favorite_count": 744,
      "_source": "dom",
      "_scraped_on": "https://x.com/Kekius_Sage/status/2054605365376160030",
      "inferred_in_reply_to_id": "2054605385210941650"
    },
    {
      "id": "2054608501696327915",
      "created_at": "2026-05-13T17:03:34.000Z",
      "text": "I like him better than NDT, but still a gatekeeper.\n\nAnything is possible now. Disclosure will be about portals. Fringe was predictive programming. Anyone who has read Raymond E. Feists's Riftwar Saga will have a head start.",
      "screen_name": "Brohonatron",
      "name": "Brohonatron",
      "pfp_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/896180594501013504/b885xRyU_400x400.jpg",
      "in_reply_to_screen_names": [],
      "media": [
